gomodel:SYNGO_5242  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figures 3-10: extensive immunogold EM showed Phocein (MOB4) localization to postsynapses (but never presynaptic terminals). subcellular localization was observed throughout the dendritic spine.\n\nauthors summarize;\n\"The present immunocytochemical study shows that phocein is strictly targeted to the dendritic spines of hippocampal pyramidal neurons and cerebellar Purkinje cells that establish asymmetric synapses with excitatory afferents in the adult brain.\". Experimental description: rats and mice were used. E.g. Figure 6 legend: \"Preembedding and postembedding immunogold detection of phocein in the cerebellar cortex of the adult rat and mouse.\". We annotate against mouse (better annotated species in uniprot).\n\nantibody:\n\"Rabbit polyclonal anti-phocein and anti-SG2NA antiserums were raised in our laboratory against affinity-purified full-length rat phocein fused to GST (GST-phocein)\"\n\nTo confirm Phocein as an alias of gene MOB4;\nPhocein characterization in PMID:17853115 links to GenBank record AJ132008 --> uniprot Q9QYW3 --> gene MOB4" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5242" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

